tmjpad (0.1.2-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Fix: TMJPad icon not appearing in v1.3.0-1 ISO despite gtk-update-icon-cache.
    Root cause: hicolor icon-theme.cache can be stale on live-CD boot
    (squashfs is read-only, cache rebuild from postinst doesn't always
    propagate to the running gnome-shell instance).
  * Solution: install the icon in 3 paths for maximum fallback coverage:
      - /usr/share/icons/hicolor/512x512/apps/tmjpad.png (matches the
        real 1024×1024 source asset; 512 is the largest standard
        hicolor bucket)
      - /usr/share/icons/hicolor/256x256/apps/tmjpad.png (legacy)
      - /usr/share/pixmaps/tmjpad.png — XDG fallback path that is
        ALWAYS consulted by Icon=name lookups regardless of cache state.
    The pixmaps fallback is what fixes the live-CD case.

 -- TMJOs Team <tmjos-archive@tmjsistemas.com.br>  Sun, 10 May 2026 22:05:00 -0300

tmjpad (0.1.1-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * First .deb-packaged release.
  * Fixes the v1.2 ISO icon-cache miss: postinst now runs
    gtk-update-icon-cache so the dedicated TMJPad icon (book +
    colored T/M/J letters) renders instead of falling back to the
    generic TMJOs logo.
  * No code changes vs the v1.2 in-ISO version — same Find/Replace,
    same persistence, same focus-on-tab behavior.

